reviewText: This movie reminds me of the kind of silly movies I used to watch as a kid. They were never very good, but they were what was available at the time, I guess. Perhaps if I were a child I might find the movie entertaining, but it seemed a bit ridiculous to me. I almost turned it off as soon as I saw that the "Luck Dragon" was really a flying dog.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I saw this movie when I was about 5 or 6. I was very enthralled in practically everything about this movie. As a child it's easy for your imagination to run wild and this movie really did a great job of capturing the imagination a child has. That said I am sad to go back to this movie as I simply cannot view it in the same way I did all those years ago. I never read the book but I know the movie ends too soon and I'm not sure why that is or why they never properly finished it. I don't care for the ending all that much. I would've liked to see more of the Fantasia that is told in this story. That being said this ranks up there with 80's fantasy classics such as The Empire Strikes Back and The Dark Crystal. There's simply nothing like watching it for the first time as a child.
Title: N/A

reviewText: The fantasy creatures are too sill for anyone over age 2.  We didn't even finish the movie, jumping forward a few times only to continue to be disappointed.  Story was engrossing but the telling of it was not good.  We don't know if even little children would be able to stay interested.
